@node history "History!"
v0.1 - 28.6.1997 - Initial Beta Release

v0.2 - 29.6.1997
       dtwrite updated, dtyp files must now start with a comment.
       During the developement of dtread (or dtwrite),
       it seems several of my dtyp's was corrupted :-( Typical!
       \0 or \? ended up where something else should be, damn!
       Wonder how many will flame me for THAT mistake.
       Turns out dtread/dtwrite messed up the signed words in the masks.
       Here are the dtyp's that have been fixed so far:
       CDXL, MPEG Video

v0.3 - 17.8.1997
       dtread will attempt to get version from datatype when no FVER
       chunk is found and the SAVEDTYP option is used,
       When the SAVEDTYP option is used, the dtbasename in the descriptor
       is ignored, and the datatype's basename itself is used.
       Removed most of the .dtyp files.
       Fixed several buggy dtyp's.
       Included several integrity tests on dtyp files for dtwrite,
       now it will complain if the Descriptor standard is violated.
       dtmake should now never create bad descriptors due to
       someone forgetting or using bad characters in names etc.
       Several undocumented features exists,
       intended to replace non-existing values with default ones,
       hopefully resulting in working descriptors when mistakes are done.
       The make scripts now will look thru subdirs of the dir chosen.
       It is no longer needed to add .dtyp to filename in dtwrite.

v0.4 - 26.8.1997
       dtwrite is now able to save 1-256 character masks, if there ever
       is need for longer ones, let me know (a hook would be better).

v1.0 - 4.10.1997
       Initial Public Release
       From now on all files in the dtmake archive,
       will have the version number of the dtmake release
       they was last changed in, so even if dtmake release v2.0 is released,
       there may still be text and scripts etc with v1.0,
       providing they work perfectly and changes are not needed :-)
@endnode

@node package "The package!"
dtmake/utils/         - @{"dtread" link "utils/dtread.txt/main"} and @{"dtwrite" link "utils/dtwrite.txt/main"} plus documentation
dtmake/scripts/       - some usefull DOS scripts
dtmake/docs/          - other documentation usefull to DataType programmers
dtmake/dtyp/          - dtyp (descriptor source) and drec (recog code) files
@endnode

@node bugs "Bugs!"
None so far!

Well, there is 1 bug! :-) With dtread, but it's not the fault of dtread.
It seems like the FVER version string in some descriptors
have spaces in the name "$VER: bla bla x.x (x.x.xx)"
Since spaces are not allowed in version string filenames,
dtread will fail and use 39.0 as default version number.
The reason it fail is the space in the name,
according to the version specs, this means the end of the name
and the start of the version number.
There is nothing I can do to fix this,
and still follow the version specs at the same time.

But this isn't a major problem, since the version number
is only for the Descriptor.
And this will not cause problems with the datatypes,
it's just damn annoying trying to figure out the descriptor version :-)
Especially since Descriptors can be changed independently of a datatype.

dtwrite fixes this problem by converting any spaces in a version name
to a lowercase "_" thus the version string dtwrite make is read correctly.

As of dtread v0.6 when the SAVEDTYP option is used,
dtread will attempt to get the datatype version if no FVER chunk
or the FVER is buggy/unreadable.
@endnode

@node introduction "Introduction!"
dtmake is a package for DataType developers.
It consist of two tools, dtread and dtwrite.
And several other files, usefull for DataType developers.

dtread allows reading of Descriptors and displaying of the info stored.
dtread is also able to disassemble a Descriptor.
dtwrite allows the creation of Descriptors.

Descriptors disassembled with dtread can be re-assembled directly.
dtread and dtwrite also handle Recog-Code and DTTL.

These two tools will be updated each time something changes
in Descriptors, i.e new chunks etc.

Included in the dtmake package is a drawer full of Descriptor sources,
ready to be edited and assembled for your own datatypes.
Even Recog-Code is inluded with some.

A list of DataType names and what those datatypes are used for,
is also included, to prevent things like a JFIF and JPEG name problem.

Note!
dtmake betas will be available to all DTA members,
members will be notified when a new version is ready.
New versions will be available from the "Msi Galactica" site
at the url: "http://www.sn.no/~msi/index.htm" on the TAC page.
This is The Amiga Concepts homepage.
@endnode

